title: Master Apache Spark 3.x using Databricks Community Edition
description:
Welcome to our comprehensive video tutorial series aimed at helping you master Apache Spark 3.x using the Databricks Community Edition. This playlist is your ultimate guide to learning how Spark can revolutionize data handling, offering a mixture of theoretical knowledge and practical applications to enhance your data skills.

Starting from the basics, we introduce you to Spark RDDs (Resilient Distributed Datasets), the fundamental building blocks of Spark applications. You‚Äôll learn how to use RDDs to perform complex data operations in a distributed environment efficiently. Next, we‚Äôll dive into the Dataframe APIs, which simplify data manipulation by offering powerful, high-level abstractions.

We‚Äôll also cover Spark SQL, a module for working with structured data. Here, you‚Äôll discover how to seamlessly query data using SQL commands in Spark, making your data analysis tasks easier and more intuitive. For those interested in the latest advancements in Spark, our tutorials include sessions on Delta Lake, an open-source storage layer that brings reliability to data lakes. Delta Lake provides ACID transactions, scalable metadata handling, and unifies streaming and batch data processing.

Continuing with cutting-edge features, our series explores Spark Structured Streaming, a scalable and fault-tolerant stream processing engine built on the Spark SQL engine. You‚Äôll learn how to handle live data streams and make real-time data-driven decisions.

Moreover, our playlist offers detailed guides on creating end-to-end applications for data pipelines. Whether you‚Äôre designing complex data transformation pipelines or building robust data integration solutions, these videos provide you with the tools and knowledge needed to succeed.

Throughout this series, our focus is on clarity and practicality, ensuring that each tutorial is easy to follow and packed with useful insights. Whether you‚Äôre a beginner looking to get started in the world of big data, or an experienced professional aiming to deepen your expertise in Apache Spark, this playlist is designed to cater to all levels.

Join us to transform your data into actionable insights and advance your career in data science and engineering. Don‚Äôt forget to subscribe and hit the notification bell to stay updated with the latest tutorials.

title: PostgreSQL SQL Full Course: Beginner to Advanced Techniques
description:
Welcome to ‚ÄúPostgreSQL SQL Full Course: Beginner to Advanced Techniques,‚Äù a definitive learning series designed to take you from a novice to a proficient user of SQL using the powerful PostgreSQL database system. This playlist is your comprehensive guide to mastering all aspects of SQL, including data definition, manipulation, and query, along with advanced features like indexing, partitioning, and optimization.

What You Will Learn:

	‚Ä¢	Introduction to PostgreSQL: Get started with PostgreSQL, understand its architecture, and learn how to install and configure it on various platforms.
	‚Ä¢	Basic SQL Operations: Dive into SQL basics with an emphasis on PostgreSQL. Learn how to create, modify, and manage databases using Data Definition Language (DDL).
	‚Ä¢	Data Manipulation Techniques: Explore Data Manipulation Language (DML) to insert, update, delete, and manage data within your databases effectively.
	‚Ä¢	Querying Data: Master Data Query Language (DQL) to retrieve data using complex SQL queries, including joins, subqueries, and common table expressions.
	‚Ä¢	Indexes and Performance Tuning: Discover how to create and manage indexes to optimize query performance. Learn best practices for analyzing and tuning queries to ensure your applications run efficiently.
	‚Ä¢	Database Design: Understand the principles of database design, normalization, and denormalization to structure your databases optimally.
	‚Ä¢	Partitioning and Sharding: Explore advanced database architectures by learning about partitioning and sharding techniques for large-scale database management.
	‚Ä¢	Practical Applications: Apply your skills through guided projects and real-world scenarios that enhance your problem-solving capabilities.

Who Should Watch This Playlist?
This playlist is tailored for students, IT professionals, software developers, and anyone eager to learn SQL using PostgreSQL. Whether you are starting your journey in database management or looking to deepen your existing SQL skills, this series offers valuable insights and practical knowledge.

Why PostgreSQL?
PostgreSQL is renowned for its robustness, feature-rich environment, and strong community support, making it an ideal learning platform for database enthusiasts and professionals. By the end of this series, you will not only be able to perform complex database tasks but also have a solid understanding of how databases work under the hood.

Join us in ‚ÄúPostgreSQL SQL Full Course: Beginner to Advanced Techniques‚Äù to unlock your potential as a database expert. Subscribe to our channel and turn on notifications to stay updated with new uploads, and don‚Äôt forget to leave your questions and comments below each video. Your feedback helps us improve and tailor our content to your learning needs.

Let‚Äôs embark on this journey together and transform your understanding and skills in SQL and PostgreSQL!

title: Databricks Certified Associate Developer - Apache Spark 3.0 using Azure (Complete Playlist)
description:
Welcome to our definitive tutorial series on mastering Apache Spark 3.0 with Databricks, tailored specifically for those preparing for the Databricks Certified Associate Developer exam using Microsoft Azure. This playlist is your ultimate guide to understanding and applying the powerful features of Apache Spark and Databricks in real-world data processing scenarios.

Start with the basics of setting up your Databricks environment on Azure, and gradually delve into more complex topics including creating and manipulating Spark DataFrames using Python, Pandas, and PySpark. Learn essential techniques such as selecting, renaming, filtering, dropping, and sorting columns within DataFrames, as well as advanced data operations like aggregations, joins, and partitioning.

Each tutorial is designed to build on the previous one, ensuring a comprehensive learning curve. We also cover the manipulation of columns and integration of Spark SQL functions for enhanced data querying and analytics. Additionally, gain insights into Spark's architecture and learn how to optimize your applications with Adaptive Query Execution for improved performance.

Whether you are a beginner looking to get started with big data technologies or an experienced developer eager to enhance your skills in Apache Spark and Databricks, this series offers valuable content to help you achieve your goals. By the end of this series, you'll be well-equipped to handle large-scale data with efficiency and confidence, making you a valuable asset in the data-driven world.

Perfect for data scientists, software developers, and IT professionals, these tutorials not only prepare you for certification but also equip you with the knowledge to apply these skills in your projects or at your workplace. Dive into our tutorials and transform your understanding and capabilities in data processing with Apache Spark and Databricks!

title: Mastering Python - A Comprehensive Python Course for beginners and experienced developers
description:
This course is primarily designed to learn Python as Programming language to build web or mobile applications, data engineering applications, automation etc.

You can access the code and material along with the videos over https://python.itversity.com

About Python

Python is one of the leading programming language. It is an open source database and used for different types of applications.

* Web Applications
* Mobile Applications
* Data Engineering Applications
* Server Automation
* Troubleshooting and Debugging
* Quality Assurance
* Data Science based Applications
and many many more

It is one of the top 3 programming languages for almost a decade now along with Java and Java Script.

Course Details

This course is primarily designed to go through core programming using Python. It will serve as foundation for role specific courses for different types of IT Professionals or Roles. As part of this course you will be learning the following topics under core programming using Python. We are actively working on creating content. Content creation for 80% of the below modules is already done. We are in the process of video editing so that we can publish the content as part of this course.

* Overview of GCP and Setup Ubuntu VM
* Setup Postgres DB using Docker
* Postgres Database Operations - Basic DDL and DML
* Getting Started with Python
* Basic Programming Constructs
* Pre Defined Functions
* User Defined Functions
* Overview of Collections - list and set
* Overview of Collections - dict and tuple
* Manipulating Collections using loops
* Overview of Map Reduce Libraries
* Overview of Pandas Libraries
* Database Programming - CRUD Operations
* Database Programming - Batch Operations
* Desired Audience

Here are the desired audience for this course.

* College students and entry level professionals to get hands on expertise with respect to programming using Python to be prepared for the interviews.
* Experienced application developers to understand key aspects of Python Programming to build Python based Web or Mobile Applications.
* Data Engineers and Data Warehouse Developers to understand key aspects of Python Programming to build batch or streaming pipelines.
* Testers to improve their scripting abilities to validate data in the files tables etc.
* DevOps Engineers, System Administrators, Database Administrators etc to understand Python as scripting language for the automation of day to day tasks.
* Data Scientists to be proficient in Python Programming to build the models.

This course only covers Fundamentals of Python which is useful for almost all the hands on technical roles. It does not include the role specific libraries.

Prerequisites

Here are the prerequisites before signing up for the course.

Logistics
* Computer with decent configuration
* At least 4 GB RAM
* 8 GB RAM is highly desired
* Browser such as Chrome, Internet Explorer, Firefox etc.
( High Speed Internet

Desired Skills

* Engineering or Science Degree
* Ability to use computer
* Knowledge or working experience with programming is highly desired

Training Approach

Here are the details related to the training approach.

* It is self paced with reference material, code snippets and videos.
* One can either use environment provided by us or setup their own environment using GCP and Docker.
* Modules will be published as and when they are ready. We would recommend to complete 2 modules every week by spending 4 to 5 hours per week.

It is highly recommended to take care of the exercises at the end to ensure that you are able to meet all the key objectives for each module.
* Support will be provided either through chat or email.
* Spend 4 to 5 hours per week up to 8 weeks and complete all the exercises to get best out of this course.

Self Evaluation

The course is designed in such a way that one can self evaluate through the course and confirm whether the skills are acquired.

Here is the approach we recommend you to take this course.

Go through the consolidated exercises and see if you are able to solve the problems or not.

Make sure to follow the order we have defined as part of the course.

After each and every section or module, make sure to solve the exercises. We have provided enough information to validate the output of your queries.

After the completion of the course try to solve the exercises using consolidated list.

Keep in mind that you will be reviewing the same exercises before the course, during the course as well as at the end of the course.

By the end of the course, if you are able to solve the problems, then you can come to a conclusion that you are able to master the core programming using one of the most popular programming language called as Python.

#MasteringPython #PythonProgramming #LearningPython #PythonLanguage #PythonFromZeroToHero

title: ITVersity - Big Data Labs - Starterkits
A comprehensive NiFi Workshop
description:
We are glad to come up with Tech Series on Mondays where we will be talking about a particular topic between 4 to 8 weeks. Some of them will be free and some of them will be paid. In case you want to get notified in case of events, please sign up to our Meetup group - https://www.meetup.com/itversityin/

NiFi is one of the key tools in the area of Data Engineering and Big Data. It is primarily used for Data Ingestion and Orchestration. As part of 6 to 8 workshops between August and September, you will be learning key capabilities. Live sessions will be free and pre-recorded videos will be available exclusively for members of our YouTube channel.

As part of the first demo, I will demonstrate key capabilities.

* Overview of NiFi
* Understanding NiFi Layout as a service
* Key Concepts such as Flow Files, Attributes etc
* Understanding how to access the documentation
* Simple pipeline to copy files from Local File System and HDFS

However, there are quite a few advanced capabilities which I will be covering as part of the Tech Workshop Series on Mondays (6 to 8 Sessions):

* Setting up of NiFi in a single node using our AMI
* Building generic data ingestion flows
* Converting File Formats
* Writing conditional flows based upon attributes
* Triggering Shell Commands or Spark Jobs
* Transforming inflight data
* Logging Attributes and Messages
* Scheduling, Monitoring, and Alerting
and many more

Key Takeaways for those who sign up for the workshop.:

* Free end to end workshop to provide data ingestion solutions using NiFi
* Details about AMI Image which can be leveraged to set up environment your selves
* Limited support using Slack

title: Building Hadoop and Spark Cluster using Ansible
description:
Quite often we have to build Big Data clusters using plain vanilla distributions rather than using vendor distributions such as Cloudera or Hortonworks. It is not practical to manually set up the cluster, rather we need to use server automation tools like Puppet, Chef or Ansible. We are going to set up a 7 node Hadoop (HDFS + YARN) cluster using Ansible.

You can access the material of the course from this link - https://kaizen.itversity.com/courses/building-hadoop-cluster-using-ansible/

Here is the agenda for the course

* Provision baremetal server and install CentOS (OVH)
* Setup single node hadoop cluster
* Setup 7 virtual machines on bare metal server using Vagrant
* Setup 7 EC2 instances on AWS
* Understand basics of Ansible
* Develop Ansible Playbook to set up binaries
* Configure HDFS on the cluster
* Configure YARN on the cluster

* IDE ‚Äì IntelliJ
* Programming Language ‚Äì Scala
* Get messages from web server log files ‚Äì logstash
* Channelize data ‚Äì Kafka (it will be covered extensively)
* Consume, process and save ‚Äì Spark Streaming using Scala as programming language
* Data store for processed data ‚Äì HBase
* Big Data Cluster ‚Äì 7 node simulated Hadoop and Spark cluster (you can also use our existing 10 node Hortonworks cluster with all related services)

Here is the flow of the course

* Setup Development Environment to build streaming applications
* Setup every thing on single node (Logstash, HDFS, Spark, Kafka etc)
* Overview of Kafka and Logstash
* Multibroker/Multi-server setup of Kafka
* Overview about Streaming technologies and Spark Streaming
* Overview of NoSQL Databases and HBase
* Development life cycle of HBase application
* Case Study: Kafka at LinkedIn
* Final Demo: Streaming Data Pipelines
